.TH DICTEE-TEST-RULES 1 "March 2026" "dictee 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dictee-test-rules \- test post-processing rules for dictee
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictee-test-rules
.RB [ \-\-loop ]
.RB [ "\-\-wav " \fIfile\fR ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dictee-test-rules
tests the post-processing rules pipeline interactively. It shows what Parakeet detects and how the rules transform the text.
.PP
When Cyrillic characters are detected in the input (common Parakeet misdetection for short commands), the tool displays the ready-to-copy rule for
.IR rules.conf .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-loop
Run in continuous test loop mode. Press Ctrl+C to exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-wav " file"
Test rules from an audio file instead of microphone input.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dictee/rules.conf
User rules configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/dictee/rules.conf.default
Default rules shipped with dictee.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dictee (1),
.BR dictee-setup (1)
